e on racial miscegenation in the context of the substantial Portuguese colonial empire; and a diffuse model of social hygiene, maternity care and puericulture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aEugenicszPortugalxHistory. 0aPortugal--Race relations--History. 0aSocial justicezPortugalxHistory. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh  aCatholic Church, Early 20th century, Eugenics, Portugal, Racial studies, Racism, Social justice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311078054340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633860298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633860298/original  a978-3-11-078054-3  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK